2011-03-04T02:55:18Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-04/philippine-stocks-aboitiz-first-philippine-metro-pacific.html
Shares of the following companies
had unusual price changes in Philippine trading. Stock symbols
are in parentheses, and prices are as of 10:46 a.m. in Manila.  The Philippine Stock Exchange Index rose 67.03, or 1.8
percent to 3,901.08.    Aboitiz Power Corp. (AP)  , a Philippine company that owns  power plants  and electricity distributors, advanced 3.5 percent
to 31.15 pesos, set for the highest close since Jan. 4. The
company said fourth-quarter profit rose 249 percent to 6.5
billion pesos ($150 million) in 2010 from a year earlier,
boosted by higher volume sales and prices.    First Philippine Holdings Corp. (FPH)  , a company with
investments in power plants, climbed 1.5 percent to 55 pesos.
The company will pay a 1 peso cash dividend, a stock exchange
filing showed.    Metro Pacific Investments Corp. (MPI)  , a unit of Hong
Kong-based First Pacific Co., increased 2.6 percent to 3.56
pesos, set for the steepest advance since Feb. 2. Metro
Pacificâ€™s profit increased 25 percent to a record 2.87 billion
pesos last year, the company said yesterday.  To contact the reporter on this story:
